description:
Using a pastiche of composed, sampled and recorded instrumentation, Newfoundland&amp;#039;s Errand Boy creates an ensemble of 13 tracks that defies the cliches of IDM and genrefication of laptop-driven music as a whole, as it draws influence and samples from everything from math rock to jewish folk music and childrens records, and leaves the listener with a varied collection of tuneful, emotional and always accessible songs which have been called &quot;lo-fi sample-driven nerd-fok.&quot;

Errand Boy&amp;#039;s first official full-length release has been compared to post-rock staples such as Do Make Say Think, Mum, and Canadian rock saviors Broken Social Scene, but filtered through an electronic lens, creating an autobiographical music diary that&amp;#039;s melancholy but inviting, and consistently refreshing. 




